  "text": "Macrophage infiltration into the injured sciatic nerve contributes to nociceptive hypersensitivity after CCI. [CITATION_1] expression of macrophage markers in the sciatic nerve at 3 and 14 days after CCI. In the locked wheel controls, we found that CCI significantly increased the expression of the macrophage marker Iba1 on day 14, but not on day 3 (P , 0.001; Fig. 4A-C) , and the chemokine CCL2 on days 3 and 14 (P , 0.001; Fig. 4D-F) . In comparison, 6 weeks of voluntary wheel running ceasing before CCI decreased the expression of Iba1 on day 14 and CCL2 on days 3 and 14 (P , 0.01; Fig. 4A-F) . However, the expression of Iba1 and CCL2 was still significantly elevated after 6 weeks of voluntary wheel running in the CCI groups on day 14, relative to the sham groups (P , 0.001; Fig. 4B, E) . A similar expression pattern was found at proximal ( Table 1 ) and distal ( Table 2) sites. Macrophages may be polarized toward either proinflammatory (M1) or anti-inflammatory (M2) phenotypes. A previous study demonstrated that 8 weeks of voluntary wheel running increases the ratio of gastrocnemius macrophages toward a M2 phenotype. [CITATION_2] Therefore, we assessed the influence of prior running on macrophage phenotype in the sciatic nerve at 3 and 14 days after CCI. The expression of an M1 marker (iNOS) and an M2 marker (Arg-1) in the injured sciatic nerve was significantly increased at 3 and 14 days after CCI in the locked wheel controls (P , 0.05; Fig.  4G-L) . We found that prior running attenuated the expression of iNOS due to CCI at both timepoints (P , 0.01; Fig. 4G, H) . Compared with CCI-locked wheel, Arg-1 expression was nonsignificantly increased on day 3 by prior running, but was significantly decreased on day 14 (P , 0.01; Fig. 4J, K) . Notably, the expression of iNOS and Arg-1 on day 14 was still elevated after 6 weeks of voluntary wheel running in the CCI groups, relative to the sham groups (P , 0.001). A similar expression pattern was found at proximal ( Table 1 ) and distal ( Table 2 ) sites, with the exception that Arg-1 was not elevated by voluntary wheel running at either site on day 3.",
